# 4. Major Subsystems

---

## A. Photonic Confinement Chamber (PCC)

### Purpose

Capture and stabilize concentrated photonic energy.

### Functions

* Photon containment
* Spectral conditioning
* Energy concentration
* Field stabilization

---

### Internal Components

```text
Reflective Containment Shell
Photon Routing Array
Confinement Grid
Field Stabilizer
```

---

### Inputs

```text
Solar Radiation
Laser Sources
Photonic Engine Output
```

---

### Outputs

```text
Conditioned Photon Field
```

---

## B. Hydrogen Interaction Module (HIM)

### Purpose

Introduce hydrogen into the energy cycle.

### Functions

* Hydrogen injection
* Energy interaction control
* Thermal generation support
* Reaction management

---

### Components

```text
Hydrogen Storage
Injection Controllers
Flow Regulators
Safety Isolation Valves
```

---

## C. HMT Spectral Stack

### Purpose

Convert incoming energy across multiple spectral layers.

### Functions

* Wavelength conditioning
* Energy redistribution
* Spectral optimization

---

### Architecture

```text
Layer 1
Photon Conditioning

Layer 2
Spectral Conversion

Layer 3
Energy Redistribution

Layer 4
Thermal Generation
```

---

## D. Thermal Generation Layer

### Purpose

Transform converted energy into controlled thermal output.

### Responsibilities

* Heat generation
* Heat routing
* Thermal buffering
* Recovery support

---

## E. TPV/PV Conversion Layer

### Purpose

Generate electrical power.

### Functions

```text
Thermal Radiation
      ↓
TPV Conversion

Photonic Radiation
      ↓
PV Conversion
```

